      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Stored is not hosted\n\nSaving a graph to GitHub stores and versions it. Publishing places a copy behind an HTTP server, such as `https://twilite.zone/company/root.node`. A hosted graph may use GitHub as its authoring source while retaining a distinct HTTPS identity. Twilite must preserve whichever address an author actually references.",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "github-guide"
        }
      }
